    {
      "id": 20,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "How to use this anomaly dashboard",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 53,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 7
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### PFE anomaly detection dashboard\n\nThis Grafana dashboard shows **live Prometheus evidence** used by the anomaly detection platform.\n\nUse it during demonstrations:\n\n- Stop the DMZ Web service/container \u2192 HTTP/TCP probes fail.\n- Stop the DNS service/container \u2192 DNS probe fails.\n- Stop or isolate a network device \u2192 SNMP device down increases.\n- Break an active interface \u2192 admin-up interface down increases.\n- Generate traffic or load \u2192 CPU/traffic panels change.\n- Interface drops/errors \u2192 error/discard panels increase.\n\n**Important:** Grafana displays metric symptoms. The exact ML decision, final hybrid decision and remediation output are generated by Jenkins and shown in the Flask dashboard/S3 artifacts.\n\nExpected safe behavior:\n\n- Rule normal + ML weak signal \u2192 human review.\n- Rule anomaly confirmed \u2192 remediation candidate.\n- Rule + ML anomaly \u2192 strongest confirmed anomaly case.\n"
      }
    }
  ],
